<subSubSection id="C348B0B0FFE61D50629806E8FE545199" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D50629806E8FEF657CF" blockId="2.[189,310,697,723]" box="[189,310,697,723]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="D0A55457FFE61D50629806E8FEF657CF" bold="true" box="[189,310,697,723]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D50629806E8FEF657CF" bold="true" box="[189,310,697,723]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D50629806B6FE545199" blockId="2.[189,1399,743,1157]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D50629806B6FE3A561E" bold="true" box="[189,506,743,770]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Antennae calceoli absent</emphasis>
. Antenna 1 longer than antenna 2; accessory flagellum absent. Mandible molar triturative, columnar; 
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D50602B075AFAAF5639" bold="true" box="[526,1391,778,805]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">palp 3-articulate, extremely elongated, article 3 longer than article 2</emphasis>
. Maxilla 1 inner plate bearing one apical seta; palp article 1 shorter than article 2. Maxilla 2 inner plate without oblique setal row. Maxilliped outer plate not reaching end margin of palp article 2. Gnathopod 1 similar in shape to gnathopod 2, slightly smaller than gnathopod 2; subchelate; carpus much shorter than propodus; with posterior lobe. Coxae 5–6 bilobate, posterior lobe larger than anterior lobe; coxa 7 rounded. 
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D50630807EAFC8C56C9" bold="true" box="[301,844,954,981]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Pereopod 5 slightly longer than pereopod 7</emphasis>
; anterior margin of propodus with bifid robust setae; dactylus simple, with small nail. Epimerons 2–3 posterior margin smooth, posteroventral corner of epimeron 2 subacute. Uropods 1–2 inner ramus longer than outer ramus, both inner and outer ramus with marginal robust setae. Uropod 3 inner ramus about twice longer than outer ramus, both inner and outer ramus with marginal robust setae, without simple or plumose setae. Telson entire, linguiform, longer than broad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C348B0B0FFE61D50629800FDFED15004" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D50629800FDFE8451DA" blockId="2.[189,324,1196,1222]" box="[189,324,1196,1222]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="D0A55457FFE61D50629800FDFE8451DA" bold="true" box="[189,324,1196,1222]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D50629800FDFE8451DA" bold="true" box="[189,324,1196,1222]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D506298008AFED15004" blockId="2.[189,1398,1243,1304]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
The generic name 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D5063BE008AFE2E51E9" authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2020" box="[411,494,1243,1269]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Bathya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D5063BE008AFE2E51E9" box="[411,494,1243,1269]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bathya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
refers to the 
<typeStatus id="54E95D99FFE61D5060AA008AFD0251E9" box="[655,706,1243,1269]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">type</typeStatus>
species designated herein that was collected from bathyal waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C348B0B0FFE61D506298016EFB525094" box="[189,1170,1343,1416]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D506298016EFE965045" blockId="2.[189,342,1343,1369]" box="[189,342,1343,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="D0A55457FFE61D506298016EFE965045" bold="true" box="[189,342,1343,1369]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D506298016EFE965045" bold="true" box="[189,342,1343,1369]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Distribution</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D506298013FFB525094" blockId="2.[189,1170,1390,1416]" box="[189,1170,1390,1416]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
North-west Pacific, Okinawa Trough, the hydrothermal vents at a depth of 
<quantity id="4CAA4EDEFFE61D50660F013FFB4E5094" box="[1066,1166,1390,1416]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.969" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" unit="m" value="996.9">996.9 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C348B0B0FFE61D51629801FEFE1954C9" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="4" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D50629801FEFEEF50D5" blockId="2.[189,303,1455,1481]" box="[189,303,1455,1481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
<heading id="D0A55457FFE61D50629801FEFEEF50D5" bold="true" box="[189,303,1455,1481]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D50629801FEFEEF50D5" bold="true" box="[189,303,1455,1481]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE61D506298018FFA975282" blockId="2.[189,1399,1502,1951]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Actually, it is a little questionable that 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D506059018FFD0F50E4" authority="Wang &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren, 2020" authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2020" box="[636,719,1502,1528]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Bathya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE61D506059018FFD0F50E4" box="[636,719,1502,1528]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Bathya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2158252FFE61D5060F0018FFCFF50E4" box="[725,831,1502,1528]" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is placed under the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D506603018FFAB750E4" authority="G. O. Sars, 1893" authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1893" box="[1062,1399,1502,1528]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Calliopiidae G.O. Sars, 1893</taxonomicName>
for having the pereopod 5 longer than pereopod 7. The phylogenetic study by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC39ECAFFE61D50667A0253FAB65307" author="Lowry J. K. &amp; Myers A. A." box="[1119,1398,1537,1564]" firstAuthor="Lowry" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 80" part="3610" refId="ref4969" refString="Lowry J. K. &amp; Myers A. A. 2013. A phylogeny and classification of the Senticaudata subord. nov. (Crustacea: Amphipoda). Zootaxa 3610 (1): 1 - 80. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3610.1.1" title="A phylogeny and classification of the Senticaudata subord. nov. (Crustacea: Amphipoda)" type="journal article" year="2013">Lowry &amp; Myers (2013)</bibRefCitation>
based on morphology analyzed showed that the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D5060CB0275FCBD5322" authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1893" box="[750,893,1572,1598]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Calliopiidae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D5061900275FAE25322" authority="Stebbing, 1906" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1906" box="[949,1314,1572,1598]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pontogeneiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pontogeneiidae Stebbing, 1906</taxonomicName>
cluster together and form a clade with 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D50601B0216FBC5537E" authority="d'Udekem d'Acoz, 2010" authorityName="d'Udekem d'Acoz" authorityYear="2010" box="[574,1029,1607,1634]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hornelliidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Hornelliidae 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC39ECAFFE61D5060FE0216FBC5537E" author="d'Udekem d'Acoz C." box="[731,1029,1607,1634]" firstAuthor="d'Udekem d'Acoz" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, Biologie" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="127 - 259" part="80" refId="ref4585" refString="d'Udekem d'Acoz C. 2010. Contribution to the knowledge of European Liljeborgiidae (Crustacea, Amphipoda), with considerations on the family and its affinities. Bulletin de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, Biologie 80: 127 - 259." title="Contribution to the knowledge of European Liljeborgiidae (Crustacea, Amphipoda), with considerations on the family and its affinities" type="journal article" year="2010">d’Udekem d’Acoz, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D5066610216FEA35399" authority="d'Udekem d'Acoz, 2010" authorityName="d'Udekem d'Acoz" authorityYear="2010" class="Malacostraca" family="Cheirocratidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Cheirocratidae 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC39ECAFFE61D5066DE0216FEA35399" author="d'Udekem d'Acoz C." firstAuthor="d'Udekem d'Acoz" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, Biologie" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="127 - 259" part="80" refId="ref4585" refString="d'Udekem d'Acoz C. 2010. Contribution to the knowledge of European Liljeborgiidae (Crustacea, Amphipoda), with considerations on the family and its affinities. Bulletin de l'Institut royal des Sciences naturelles de Belgique, Biologie 80: 127 - 259." title="Contribution to the knowledge of European Liljeborgiidae (Crustacea, Amphipoda), with considerations on the family and its affinities" type="journal article" year="2010">d’Udekem d’Acoz, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The new genus is not listed under 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D50613D023AFC055399" authorityName="d'Udekem d'Acoz" authorityYear="2010" box="[792,965,1643,1669]" class="Malacostraca" family="Cheirocratidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cheirocratidae</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D5061D7023AFB485399" authorityName="d'Udekem d'Acoz" authorityYear="2010" box="[1010,1160,1643,1669]" class="Malacostraca" family="Hornelliidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hornelliidae</taxonomicName>
, which are also not having antennae calceoli, for having the following characteristics: the inner plate of maxilla 1 only bearing apical seta, maxilla 2 without oblique setal row, the rami of uropod 3 unequal in length, and the entire telson. The new genus is not suited to be placed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D50617D0285FBCD53F2" authorityName="Stebbing" authorityYear="1906" box="[856,1037,1748,1774]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pontogeneiidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pontogeneiidae</taxonomicName>
for the propodus of gnathopod 2 having robust setae along the palmar margin. Moreover, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D50615002A6FB5E520D" authority="Lowry, 2006" authorityName="Lowry" authorityYear="2006" box="[885,1182,1783,1810]" class="Malacostraca" family="Sanchoidae" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">
Sanchoidae 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC39ECAFFE61D50662102A9FB5E520D" author="Lowry J. K." box="[1028,1182,1783,1810]" firstAuthor="Lowry" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 28" part="1254" refId="ref4815" refString="Lowry J. K. 2006. New families and subfamilies of Amphipod Crustaceans. Zootaxa 1254: 1 - 28." title="New families and subfamilies of Amphipod Crustaceans" type="journal article" year="2006">Lowry, 2006</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which are known as endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="F345A3ABFFE61D506342034AFE135229" box="[359,467,1819,1845]" name="Australia" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Australia</collectingCountry>
and associated with sponges (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC39ECAFFE61D50611F034AFB975229" author="Lowry J. K. &amp; Barnard J. L." box="[826,1111,1819,1845]" firstAuthor="Lowry" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Crustacean Biology" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="231 - 242" part="21" refId="ref4837" refString="Lowry J. K. &amp; Barnard J. L. 2001. Revision of the endemic Australian genus Sancho (Amphipoda, Eusiridae). Journal of Crustacean Biology 21 (1): 231 - 242. https: // doi. org / 10.1651 / 0278 - 0372 (2001) 021 [0231: ROTEAG] 2.0. CO; 2" title="Revision of the endemic Australian genus Sancho (Amphipoda, Eusiridae)" type="journal article" year="2001">Lowry &amp; Barnard 2001</bibRefCitation>
), have been listed under the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D5062CD036FFEBB5244" authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1893" box="[232,379,1854,1880]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Calliopiidae</taxonomicName>
. However, the present genus cannot be incorporated in this family for the lack of a nonrecessed head and a dorsoventrally flattened urosome (
<bibRefCitation id="EFC39ECAFFE61D5061600330FC1D5260" author="Lowry J. K." box="[837,989,1889,1916]" firstAuthor="Lowry" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" pagination="1 - 28" part="1254" refId="ref4815" refString="Lowry J. K. 2006. New families and subfamilies of Amphipod Crustaceans. Zootaxa 1254: 1 - 28." title="New families and subfamilies of Amphipod Crustaceans" type="journal article" year="2006">Lowry 2006</bibRefCitation>
). Hence, it is more reasonable that this new genus is to be placed under 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE61D50604803D5FD3C5282" authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1893" box="[621,764,1924,1950]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Calliopiidae</taxonomicName>
with an emendation of the diagnosis of this family.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEDE33BFFE71D516298055AFE1954C9" blockId="3.[189,1399,267,469]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">
Besides having the pereopod 5 longer than pereopod 7, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE71D51615C055AFC0C5439" authority="Wang &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren, 2020" authorityName="Wang &amp; Zhu &amp; Sha &amp; Ren" authorityYear="2020" box="[889,972,267,293]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" genus="Bathya" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9263F29FFE71D51615C055AFC0C5439" box="[889,972,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="4">Bathya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2158252FFE71D5161FD055DFB88543A" box="[984,1096,268,294]" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be distinguished its congeners of the 
<taxonomicName id="4C5298B8FFE71D5163AF057FFDD95454" authorityName="G. O. Sars" authorityYear="1893" box="[394,537,302,328]" class="Malacostraca" family="Calliopiidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="3" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Calliopiidae</taxonomicName>
by having the combination of the following characters: eyes present but not well pigmented; antenna 1 longer than antenna 2; the absence of an accessory flagellum; the inner plate of maxilla 1 only bearing one apical seta; maxilla 2 without oblique setal row; gnathopod 1 similar in shape and size to gnathopod 2; pleonites 1–3 without dorsal carinae; the rami of uropod 3 unequal in length; the entire telson.
</paragraph>
